[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] The object made by pairing up `keys` and `values`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Creates a new object from a list key-value pairs.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] If a key appears in multiple pairs, the rightmost pair is included in the object.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] An object with the output of `fn` for keys, mapped to arrays of elements that produced that key when passed to `fn`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Splits a list into sub-lists stored in an object, based on the result of calling a key-returning function on each element, and grouping the results according to values returned.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Dispatches to the `groupBy` method of the second argument, if present.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] A list that contains sublists of elements, whose concatenations are equal to the original list.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Takes a list and returns a list of lists where each sublist's elements are all satisfied pairwise comparison according to the provided function.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Only adjacent elements are passed to the comparison function.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns `true` if the first argument is greater than the second; `false` otherwise.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns `true` if the first argument is greater than or equal to the second; `false` otherwise.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns whether or not a path exists in an object.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Only the object's own properties are checked.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns the first element of the given list or string.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] In some libraries this function is named `first`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns true if its arguments are identical, false otherwise.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Values are identical if they reference the same memory.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] `NaN` is identical to `NaN`; `0` and `-0` are not identical.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Note this is merely a curried version of ES6 `Object.is`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] `identical` does not support the `__` placeholder.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] A function that does nothing but return the parameter supplied to it.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Good as a default or placeholder function.
