[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Creates a function that will process either the `onTrue` or the `onFalse` function depending upon the result of the `condition` predicate.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Note that `ifElse` takes its arity from the longest of the three functions passed to it.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] `true` if an equivalent item is in the list, `false` otherwise.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns `true` if the specified value is equal, in `R.equals` terms, to at least one element of the given list; `false` otherwise.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] An object indexing each array element by the given property.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Given a function that generates a key, turns a list of objects into an object indexing the objects by the given key.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Note that if multiple objects generate the same value for the indexing key only the last value will be included in the generated object.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] the index of the target, or -1 if the target is not found.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns the position of the first occurrence of an item in an array, or -1 if the item is not included in the array.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Returns all but the last element of the given list or string.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Takes a predicate `pred`, a list `xs`, and a list `ys`, and returns a list `xs'` comprising each of the elements of `xs` which is equal to one or more elements of `ys` according to `pred`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] `pred` must be a binary function expecting an element from each list.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] `xs`, `ys`, and `xs'` are treated as sets, semantically, so ordering should not be significant, but since `xs'` is ordered the implementation guarantees that its values are in the same order as they appear in `xs`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Duplicates are not removed, so `xs'` may contain duplicates if `xs` contains duplicates.
