[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Takes a string-returning function `keyGen` and a function `fn` and returns a new function that returns cached results for subsequent calls with the same arguments.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] When the function is invoked, `keyGen` is applied to the same arguments and its result becomes the cache key.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] If the cache contains something under that key, the function simply returns it and does not invoke `fn` at all.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Otherwise `fn` is applied to the same arguments and its return value is cached under that key and returned by the function.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p02] Care must be taken when implementing `keyGen` to avoid key collision, or if tracking references, memory leaks and mutating arguments.
