[src:ramda-functional/page-p03] A transducer is a function that accepts a transformer and returns a transformer and can be composed directly.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p03] A transformer is an object that provides a 2-arity reducing iterator function, step, 0-arity initial value function, init, and 1-arity result extraction function, result.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p03] The result function is used to convert the final accumulator into the return type and in most cases is `R.identity`.
[src:ramda-functional/page-p03] The init function can be used to provide an initial accumulator, but is ignored by transduce.
